  <scopecontent id="aspace_36ed8e240526b0b2d950a6e3fbf5e58e">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Photocopies of newspaper clippings concerning the Maine Sugar Industries, Inc., the Finger Lakes Sugar Beet Growers Association, and unsuccessful attempts to develop a sugar beet industry in central New York. Includes photographs, bulletin preparation materials, correspondence, notes, and a research proposal about the project. Also includes two films: "The Root of Progress" and "Introducing Sugar Beets," tables, scrapbooks, and additional correspondence, photographs, and bulletins.</p><p> Also, "Finger Lakes Sugar Beet Growers Association and Pepsi-Cola Company Present the Story of Beet Sugar. Authors: C. L. Swanson and J. T. Bugbee Through the Courtesy of Texaco's Magazine Lubrication."</p>  </scopecontent>
  <odd id="aspace_a36386b5b580d47753dc3ae3b283e175">
    <head>NOTES</head>
<p>Material was collected by Gould Colman and Theodore Bateman.</p>  </odd>
